@a3 2
  - AdditionalMessage
  - MFC TestRunner bug fixes
d6 2
d9 1
a9 10
  - HelperMacros

* Asserter:
  
  - A new AdditionalMessage class has been introduced. It is used for
    assertion that takes an additional 'message' argument. Since this
    macro has an implicit constructor that take a string, which creates
    a Message with the specified string as detail. That way, additional
    message can be a single string or a complex Message object. See
    documentation for example of use.
a27 8
* Failure diagnostic

  - setUp() and tearDown() now provides a detailed diagnostic of the
    failure (assertion, exception...)

  - If RTTI is allowed to extract type info, CppUnit will report the
    actual exception type in the diagnostic.

